  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently in heavy gamma selling mode with SPX at 6585.96 sitting below the massive +65.3B gamma wall at 6600, creating strong magnetic pull toward that strike as dealers hedge short gamma by buying the underlying. The PIN regime with 102B total GEX suggests dealers will aggressively fade any move above 6600 by selling into strength, while the negative gamma pocket at 6570 (-30.5B) acts as a volatility accelerant if breached to the downside. \n\nWatch for chop between 6590-6600 as the clustered positive gamma walls create a stabilizing zone, but any break above 6611 (GEX flip) shifts dealers to gamma buying mode and could trigger momentum acceleration higher.",
